At this point, the Speaker (Council Member Quinn) asked for a Moment of Silence for the following individuals:

Sgt. Deon Taylor, 30 of the Bronx,  (CM Arroyo's District) killed in action in Afghanistan;
Jamel Spears, 33, New York City Probationary Firefighter, died in training drill;
Daniel DeFrancesco, 68, former long-time Director of the Board of Elections;
Terence Tolbert, 44, well-known NYC public servant, died while serving as Barack Obama's campaign director in Nevada;
Walter Stafford, 68, well-known Professor of Urban Planning & Public Policy at the NYU  Wagner School of Public Service;
Former New York City Council Member Philip Reed, 59, who died of cancer--he served in the Council from 1998 to 2005.
